{
  "text": "The dose of sertraline used in this study was 50mg, but doses as high as 200mg/d are commonly used in clinical practice to treat some psychiatric disorders [CITATION_1] . It is possible that higher doses of sertraline could affect beneficial hemodynamic changes in POTS patients. These potential benefits would have to be balanced against the potential increase in adverse effects associated with higher doses of sertraline, and requires further study.",
  "correct_citation": {
